# Working with Code

Polyester handles code blocks seamlessly - curly braces inside code fences won't break the parser.

## JavaScript Example

```javascript
function createDocument(options = {}) {
  const { title, author, date } = options;

  return {
    metadata: {
      title: title || 'Untitled',
      author: author || 'Anonymous',
      createdAt: date || new Date()
    },
    sections: [],
    addSection(name, content) {
      this.sections.push({ name, content });
      return this;
    }
  };
}

// Usage
const doc = createDocument({ title: 'My Report' })
  .addSection('intro', 'Welcome!')
  .addSection('body', 'Content here...');

console.log(doc);
```

